01:13:05.939 --> 01:13:07.939
I meditate on all your activity.

01:13:07.939 --> 01:13:10.939
I eagerly ponder over the work of your hands.

01:13:11.939 --> 01:13:13.939
I spread out my hands to you.

01:13:13.939 --> 01:13:19.939
I am like a parched land that thirsts for you.

01:13:19.939 --> 01:13:22.939
So David thirsted for Jehovah.

01:13:22.939 --> 01:13:26.939
Thirst for Jehovah as a parched land thirsts for water.

01:13:26.939 --> 01:13:28.939
Water makes the land revive.

01:13:28.939 --> 01:13:30.939
It makes it flourish.

01:13:30.939 --> 01:13:34.939
Like a dry, crusty riverbed in Africa is revived in flourishes

01:13:34.939 --> 01:13:37.939
when distant rains come and saturate the soil.

01:13:37.939 --> 01:13:41.939
So we want to satisfy our thirst for Jehovah on a daily basis.

01:13:41.939 --> 01:13:42.939
How?

01:13:42.939 --> 01:13:43.939
How do we do that?

01:13:43.939 --> 01:13:48.939
Well, we want to continue to learn more about our father on a daily basis,

01:13:48.939 --> 01:13:50.939
digging into his word.

01:13:50.939 --> 01:13:52.939
Hosea 6 verse 3 says that,

01:13:52.939 --> 01:13:55.939
we will know, we will earnestly seek to know Jehovah.

01:13:55.939 --> 01:13:57.939
He will come to us like a pouring rain,

01:13:57.939 --> 01:14:02.939
like a spring rain that saturates the earth.

01:14:02.939 --> 01:14:06.939
Even at Gilead, you have only learned the fringes of Jehovah's ways.

01:14:07.939 --> 01:14:11.939
So there's so much more that's available through the organization,

01:14:11.939 --> 01:14:13.939
through Jehovah's organization.

01:14:13.939 --> 01:14:15.939
Keep thirsting, keep learning.

01:14:15.939 --> 01:14:18.939
So learning about Jehovah, another thing,

01:14:18.939 --> 01:14:21.939
maintain a regular routine of prayer.

01:14:21.939 --> 01:14:26.939
Pray constantly is what first Thessalonians 5 verse 17 tells us.

01:14:26.939 --> 01:14:28.939
The study note Paul says,

01:14:28.939 --> 01:14:31.939
Paul was not expecting the Thessalonians to pray at every moment.

01:14:31.939 --> 01:14:35.939
Rather, he was encouraging them to have a prayerful attitude.

01:14:35.939 --> 01:14:37.939
So thirst for Jehovah.

01:14:37.939 --> 01:14:40.939
Keep your relationship with him close.

01:14:40.939 --> 01:14:42.939
Always look to Jehovah.

01:14:42.939 --> 01:14:45.939
And will Jehovah satisfy your thirst for him?

01:14:45.939 --> 01:14:47.939
Absolutely.

01:14:47.939 --> 01:14:51.939
We can learn something from what occurred in Samson's life.

01:14:51.939 --> 01:14:53.939
It's found in judges chapter 15.

01:14:53.939 --> 01:15:00.699
And just as we had assurance earlier that Jehovah will care for your spiritual hunger,

01:15:00.699 --> 01:15:03.699
he will care for your thirst as well.

01:15:03.699 --> 01:15:05.699
In chapter 15, interestingly,

01:15:05.699 --> 01:15:08.699
verses 17 through 19, Samson's life,

01:15:08.699 --> 01:15:16.140
he had just experienced, as the verse says,

01:15:16.140 --> 01:15:18.140
Jehovah's spirit empowered him.

01:15:18.140 --> 01:15:20.140
He became absorbed in a Theocratic assignment,

01:15:20.140 --> 01:15:22.140
fighting Jehovah's enemies, the Philistines,

01:15:22.140 --> 01:15:24.140
and with the jawbone of a donkey,

01:15:24.140 --> 01:15:26.140
killed 1,000 Philistines.

01:15:26.140 --> 01:15:27.140
Then what?

01:15:27.140 --> 01:15:28.140
Verse 17 says,

01:15:28.140 --> 01:15:29.140
when he finished speaking,

01:15:29.140 --> 01:15:32.140
he threw the jawbone away and he called the place,

01:15:32.140 --> 01:15:34.140
and he called on Jehovah and said,

01:15:34.140 --> 01:15:36.140
it was you who gave this great salvation

01:15:36.140 --> 01:15:37.140
into the hand of your servant.

01:15:37.140 --> 01:15:39.140
But now, am I to die of thirst and fall

01:15:39.140 --> 01:15:41.140
into the hands of the uncircumcised?

01:15:41.140 --> 01:15:45.140
So God split open a hollow that was in Lehigh

01:15:45.140 --> 01:15:47.140
and water flowed from it.

01:15:47.140 --> 01:15:49.140
When he drank,

01:15:49.140 --> 01:15:52.140
his spirit returned, and he revived.

01:15:52.140 --> 01:15:55.140
That is why he named the place,

01:15:55.140 --> 01:15:57.140
and Hakkori,

01:15:57.140 --> 01:15:59.140
which is in the name of Jesus.

01:15:59.140 --> 01:16:00.140
He named the place,

01:16:00.140 --> 01:16:01.140
and Hakkori,

01:16:01.140 --> 01:16:04.140
which is in Lehigh to this day.

01:16:04.140 --> 01:16:06.140
And Hakkori,

01:16:06.140 --> 01:16:08.140
where Jehovah's split open a hollow

01:16:08.140 --> 01:16:10.140
to satisfy Samson's thirst,

01:16:10.140 --> 01:16:11.140
his spirit returned.

01:16:11.140 --> 01:16:12.140
He revived.

01:16:12.140 --> 01:16:14.140
So what's the point?

01:16:14.140 --> 01:16:19.140
There's no antitipical jawbone of a donkey, no.

01:16:19.140 --> 01:16:21.140
But in future days,

01:16:21.140 --> 01:16:24.140
you will certainly be busy in Theocratic assignments,

01:16:24.140 --> 01:16:27.140
just as Samson was.

01:16:27.140 --> 01:16:30.140
Be sure to return to end Hakkori,

01:16:30.140 --> 01:16:33.140
regularly, and revive your spirit

01:16:33.140 --> 01:16:35.140
by drawing close to our God.

01:16:35.140 --> 01:16:38.140
He is a lifeline to your success.

01:16:38.140 --> 01:16:40.140
Stay hungry.

01:16:40.140 --> 01:16:42.140
Stay thirsty.

