01:18:02.140 --> 01:18:04.140
For this month's postcard,

01:18:04.140 --> 01:18:08.119
we travel to the Netherlands.

01:18:08.119 --> 01:18:10.119
The Netherlands means

01:18:10.119 --> 01:18:12.119
the lowlands,

01:18:12.119 --> 01:18:14.119
a fitting name for a country

01:18:14.119 --> 01:18:16.119
of more than a quarter of its land

01:18:16.119 --> 01:18:18.119
below sea level,

01:18:18.119 --> 01:18:20.119
and nearly 20%

01:18:20.119 --> 01:18:22.119
iconic windmills

01:18:22.119 --> 01:18:24.119
and wooden shoes are reminders

01:18:24.119 --> 01:18:26.119
that managing water

01:18:26.119 --> 01:18:28.119
is a way of life here.

01:18:28.119 --> 01:18:30.119
An ingenious system

01:18:30.119 --> 01:18:32.119
of dunes, dikes, pumps,

01:18:32.119 --> 01:18:34.119
and barriers protects against floods.

01:18:34.119 --> 01:18:36.119
Life's water

01:18:36.119 --> 01:18:38.119
of Bible truth started flowing

01:18:38.119 --> 01:18:40.119
into this land

01:18:40.119 --> 01:18:42.119
in the early 1900s.

01:18:42.119 --> 01:18:44.119
By the beginning of World War II,

01:18:44.119 --> 01:18:48.119
there were about 500 Jehovah's Witnesses here.

01:18:48.119 --> 01:18:50.119
They offered severe persecution

01:18:50.119 --> 01:18:52.119
by the Occupy Nazis.

01:18:52.119 --> 01:18:54.119
Over 300

01:18:54.119 --> 01:18:56.119
of our brothers were deported

01:18:56.119 --> 01:18:58.119
to concentration camps.

01:18:58.119 --> 01:19:00.119
Sadly,

01:19:00.119 --> 01:19:02.119
more than 130 of them died.

01:19:02.119 --> 01:19:04.119
Despite these challenges,

01:19:04.119 --> 01:19:06.119
with Jehovah's help,

01:19:06.119 --> 01:19:08.119
and the faithful stand

01:19:08.119 --> 01:19:10.119
of our brothers and sisters,

01:19:10.119 --> 01:19:12.119
the preaching work accelerated.

01:19:12.119 --> 01:19:16.119
In August 1945,

01:19:16.119 --> 01:19:18.119
at the first convention held

01:19:18.119 --> 01:19:20.119
after the war,

01:19:20.119 --> 01:19:22.119
4,000 were in attendance.

01:19:22.119 --> 01:19:24.119
Today,

01:19:24.119 --> 01:19:26.119
about 30,000 witnesses

01:19:26.119 --> 01:19:28.119
zealously preach here.

01:19:28.119 --> 01:19:30.119
The number of regular

01:19:30.119 --> 01:19:32.119
and special pioneers

01:19:32.119 --> 01:19:34.119
increased a total of 36%

01:19:34.119 --> 01:19:36.119
in the last three years.

01:19:36.119 --> 01:19:38.119
You'll see bicycles

01:19:38.119 --> 01:19:40.119
just about everywhere in the Netherlands.

01:19:40.119 --> 01:19:42.119
Nearly 30%

01:19:42.119 --> 01:19:44.119
of all journeys are made by bicycle.

01:19:44.119 --> 01:19:46.119
Our brothers and sisters

01:19:46.119 --> 01:19:48.119
love to engage in the ministry

01:19:48.119 --> 01:19:50.119
on two wheels.

01:19:50.119 --> 01:19:52.119
In a country known for its

01:19:52.119 --> 01:19:54.119
many waterways,

01:19:54.119 --> 01:19:56.119
publishers preach from boat to boat

01:19:56.119 --> 01:19:58.119
and from ship to ship,

01:19:58.119 --> 01:20:00.119
such as in Rotterdam,

01:20:00.119 --> 01:20:04.119
which manages the biggest harbor in Europe.

01:20:04.119 --> 01:20:06.119
We end our visit in Layden,

01:20:06.119 --> 01:20:08.119
a beautiful historic city.

01:20:08.119 --> 01:20:10.119
This is where the famous

01:20:10.119 --> 01:20:12.119
Dutch painter Rembrandt

01:20:12.119 --> 01:20:14.119
was born in 1606.

01:20:14.119 --> 01:20:16.119
One of the two congregations

01:20:16.119 --> 01:20:18.119
in Layden is Decoy.

01:20:18.119 --> 01:20:20.119
Their territory is

01:20:20.119 --> 01:20:22.119
close to the tool of fields,

01:20:22.119 --> 01:20:24.119
which bloom from April to May

01:20:24.119 --> 01:20:26.119
and attract millions of tourists

01:20:26.119 --> 01:20:28.119
every year.

01:20:28.119 --> 01:20:30.119
Traditional Dutch cuisine is known

01:20:30.119 --> 01:20:32.119
for herring,

01:20:32.119 --> 01:20:34.119
pastries, and strupe waffles.

01:20:34.119 --> 01:20:36.119
A delicious treat made up

01:20:36.119 --> 01:20:38.119
of two waffle cookies

01:20:38.119 --> 01:20:40.119
held together by syrup.

01:20:40.119 --> 01:20:42.119
The Dutch cheeses are known

01:20:42.119 --> 01:20:44.119
throughout the world,

01:20:44.119 --> 01:20:46.119
including Adam

01:20:46.119 --> 01:20:48.119
and Howda,

01:20:48.119 --> 01:20:50.119
named for the towns in which they

01:20:50.119 --> 01:20:52.119
originated.

01:20:52.119 --> 01:20:54.119
Many of the Decoy

01:20:54.119 --> 01:20:56.119
congregations, 129 publishers,

01:20:56.119 --> 01:20:58.119
visited the picturesque

01:20:58.119 --> 01:21:00.119
Mirberger-Molen-Wennmill

01:21:00.119 --> 01:21:02.119
to send you their love

01:21:02.119 --> 01:21:04.119
and affection.

